      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;in my humble, estimation, a rouge is a thief. What better way to increase the rogues usefullness to the game in toto than pickpocketing?&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Just a suggestion.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Make an entirely new loot table, accessible only to those who can pickpocket. if the mob dies and no rogue has successfully picked his pocket, that particular loot is gone and doesnt transfer to the main loot table for that mob.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;What to put in the new loot table?&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;money? nah! too many other ways to make money.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;How about, a specific line of small ticket items. such as jewelry,&amp;nbsp; gems, spells, things a person would normally have in their pockets.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;At the largest in size, a small knife perhaps. Other things would fit better into the game and into the perception of reality here,&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;glowing black stones, rare gems, spell pages, a rock, a knucklebone from some poor unfortunate soul the mob ate right before meeting you, a toothpick. The list goes on and on in EQ. you have so many items in the game and hardly many ways to earn them. &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;This would allow the rogue to always remain on his toes, wondering what the pickpocket ability could possibly grant him. some no drop items, some items he could sell. some he would consider using, or some part of a tradeskill.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
