    <item>
      <title>Rappin' Rogue Revealed.. Unconcealed.. but still keepin' it real</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Rogue&amp;message.id=4338#M4338</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;I've read a lot of the stuff here, but not all. I may not offer any new ideas, but I will mention what my own personal preferences are for rogues, and some of the things that I think ought to be done (or should have been done long ago). As far as I am concerned, rogues are a broken class at this point and there is no question that there needs to be *major* changes to the class or to the game itself in order for them to be a class worth playing on a full time basis.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;So.. starting with that caveat.. the main problem with rogues as I see it is that their only consistent and practical contribution to groups and raids is: DPS. (They are one-hit wonders....) Which, of course, is not a problem when they are far and away the best DPS class.. which, of course, they are not. Other classes have close to, and, in many cases, more DPS than rogues do (without the wonder part).. but their contributions don't end there.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;So.. since we have been forbidden to make an argument for more DPS, we are left with ways in which rogues can contribute beyond DPS, that could be equivalent to the ways in which other high DPS classes contribute. All right.. just to get an idea of what kind of gap, or deficit, we are looking at in non-dps abilities.. let me suggest that:&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Rogues be given the ability to slow undead, to rez fallen companions, to heal the group with a clicky orb that they can summon, to singlehandedly do Nest and various other DoD missions; be given a pet (that we can use to pull singles with, and off tank adds with), cast Disease/Poison Resists/Levitation buffs, summon corpses, self-evac with no timer or need to be sneak/hidden, snare, root, give other classes mana, gate, cast short term group wide attack buffs, debuff mobs, a free ability to lose all aggro through feign death, pull mobs via feign death, oh... and to open up TWO chests on the MPG Subversion Trial.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;So, would SoE consider giving those abilities to rogues? No.. that would be *RIDICULOUS* wouldn't it? To give a class with the *highest* dps in *many* situations all of THAT, &lt;U&gt;TOO&lt;/U&gt;!&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;(Oh by the way, and I'm NOT asking for &lt;U&gt;MORE&lt;/U&gt; DPS here, could you just make it so AE Rampage and mob 'push' has little to no effect upon our DPS output? And make it so our existing DPS output is not mitigated by any drain we put upon a healer's time and mana on raids?) --Yes, a few mobs are resistant --&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;They couldn't give us all of those abilities anyway, because they belong to another class. Now.. let's look at what rogues can do.. *besides* DPS.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Picking pockets and locks, disarming traps, Sneak/Hide, Escape, ability to self-evac, and a short term (6 second?) mez. Poisons. The ability to set a "trap".&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;How much do these abilities contribute practically speaking?&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Very little, in my opinion.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Pockets are not worth picking. There are few, if any missions, where picking pockets is required, helpful, or even *possible* in order to complete it. When I got past level 20, I've used the skill twice (both as a required part of the rogue epic).&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Locks are rumored to exist in Everquest, but are believed to be limited to only the remotest of zones, and to be guarded by vicious, green conning rats, frogloks, and skeletons. Occasionally, one will receive an urgent tell requesting your assistance in picking such a lock in &amp;lt;insert remote, middle of nowhere zone&amp;gt;. This, along with dragging corpses, is one of the few shining moments in the life of a serious Assassin. Well, there's always subversion trial.. oh.. but we can only open up ONE. :(&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;"Traps, traps.. everywhere traps!.. Careful guys.. don't MOVE!.. I'm serious.. My spider senses are tingling.. I sense a trap in THIS direction! /me points!"&lt;BR&gt;Traps.. ahh.. the traps.. so CRITICAL to the work of a rogue.. that we were blessed with a new 12 AA ability in order to detect them. Thank Bristlebane! I'll let y'all know if I find any.. I'm ALWAYS looking! :-)!!&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Sneak/Hide is useful, at least relative to our other abilities which have next to no use. and is certainly something that contributes to adventuring in EQ. It is rather &lt;I&gt;limited&lt;/I&gt; in it's uses, but it is at least *fairly* useful.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Escape is cool. It's on a timer, so it's not *particularly* useful. Can pull (once every 15 minutes or so) if you get a lucky split... but it's no feign death.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Self-evac is also cool. It's set on a long timer, that can be used only under the condition that you are not currently being attacked, and that you have been hidden for a certain amount of time, but.. you can use it to get out of some situation and for traveling... but it's no Levant.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;ASSASSIN'S FEINT.. ooooh!.. Ahhhh!.. Hell yeah! Time to get SERIOUS about our roles as the ASSASSINS of Norrath! Oh.. see.. I saw the word Assasssin and... well.. nm.. Rogues can mez a mob for a short period of time. And honestly, I like it, to a degree. It *has* it's uses. It can interrupt some mobs casting gate.. it can help buy the enchanter or necro (who can kite adds) or whoever.. the time to deal with the add. It's also good for when you *want* to get aggro. It's kind of cool.. It was useful on creators, but now I do nests.. and on Nests.. it has no use whatsoever. This is also true of the rogue's ability to assassinate.. was really cool back in Sebilis.. but at level 70 is next to useless. Unlike Assassinate, however, rogue mez is not necessarily "roguelike".. at the very least.. it's a bit of a stretch. But.. I still found it very useful in DoN and to a certain extent now.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Poisons.. another staple of rogues.. as far as their contributions beyond DPS (itself rather limited) is.. well.. rather limited. I think there's a mob that can only be slowed by a rogue poison or something, but I haven't personally dealth with it. I've spent a fair amount of time making them, but can't really think of many contributions they make.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Oooh.. TRAPS.. TRAPS.. TRAPS.. and NOW.. rogues have their very OWN! We can be ASSASSINS now! Well... as excited as *I* was initially about our trap.. I now see it more as a cute gag to play on raids and in groups. Easy laughs.. good times.. good times.. Apparently, they prefer that the necromancer remain on snare duty.. and that I should focus my efforts more on standing behind the mobs and backstabbing them.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;In fact.. even with all of those abilities I mentioned.. 95% of the time.. that's all that I'm asked to do as a rogue.. stand behind it.. and backstab it. Sometimes I'll drag a corpse (for the fd necro to rez), scout ahead (backstabbing the Eye of Zemm otw), do a stealthy turn in, etc.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;In the grand scheme of things, you take away a rogue's DPS and you've got a jackass with a lockpick in a world with few locks. You take away a necromancers DPS and they are *still* overpowered. That is the reality.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Bottom Line:&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Please spare us this idea that rogues are being unreasonable in their dissatisfaction with their DPS.... as it is, relative to *other* abilities and contributions in this game. The deficit in rogues utility beyond DPS is ENORMOUS. If you do NOT give them an *enormous* DPS increase, then you will need to either *fundamentally* change the mechanics of this game in order to make traps and locks and pickpocketing, etc. *enormously* useful.. OR.. give Rogues *super powers* that allow them to do things that are of *enormous* value and utility.. but are utterly unroguelike.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Honestly, I am OK with not receiving an ENORMOUS DPS increase. Rogues are Assassins, but that doesn't necessarily mean they should always be the kings of DPS. If Oswald and Boothe MISSED.. then their DPS would have been rather low, wouldn't it? So, I'm ok with that... I think rogues *should* be able to assassinate higher level mobs.. *sometimes*.. like in the old days in Sebilis. But.. to be highest in sustained damage over time.. all the time.. that isn't necessarily what rogues *ought* to be, imo.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;However.. are you *going* to make our poisons USEFUL? To actually have an *impact* on the game in a way that makes their use integral to being a rogue? Are you *going* to make our traps.. TRAPS? We are rogues, the undisputed &lt;I&gt;experts&lt;/I&gt; at traps.. and a *necromancer* who has *absolutely nothing* to do with traps in any way, shape, or form... gets a *trap* that does DPS, albeit limited? And the Assassin's trap snares? Are you going to program traps that are placed *randomly* (not fixed and predictable ones) in zones where a rogue would be of enormous use in disarming? Are you going to create missions that allow the possibility of stealth and the skilled pickpocketing of items in order to progress through them? Or perhaps items of real value that can be pickpocketed from various mobs in cities and various other zones across Norrath? More consistent with the idea of deception, trickery, and manipulation.. will you give rogues the ability to distract the attention of one mob so that the other mob can be pulled? (As in throwing a rock to make a noise of some kind that the mobs would go and investigate.. that seems roguelike to me).&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Personally, I'm not interested in unroguelike *super powers* to create an artificial utility. Pulling makes sense to me.. whereas.. mezzing/crowd control does not. Instead of creating clever gimmiks like Beastlords and Berserkers and traps and breakable objects and all of the other advertised, underdeveloped features on your game boxes.. will you all actually take the time to change the nature of the game to accomdate rogues and their roguelike abilities? If so, I'm all for it.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;But if you &lt;I&gt;aren't&lt;/I&gt; going to do *that*.. which you have not done in the many years this game has been in existence then give us what you ALWAYS have.. until recently: DPS &lt;U&gt;mastery&lt;/U&gt;. Or give us Super Powers! But.. one way or another, you need to make rogues worth playing again. &lt;I&gt;My&lt;/I&gt; account will remain inactive while you all work out the details...&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Shadowpiercer&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;!--  / message  --&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
